Suzhou is now the largest city-economy in Jiangsu Province and a manufacturing powerhouse in the Yangtze Delta Region. Through foreign direct investment and high-end manufacturing, Suzhou maintains long-term, high-quality growth, accounting for a fifth of the overall economy in Jiangsu Province. This year, city officials have set a growth target of 5 percent for Suzhou. Now how is the city going to achieve that goal? In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Zheng Junfeng explains.